    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"modern sociological approach\" you're mentioning sounds a lot like you're saying the old way was just wrong. If the evidence is so overwhelmingly pointing towards root causes, isn't it basically a settled issue? Like, why are we even still debating it as a valid policy option if the data shows it's ineffective and just causes more harm to specific groups?",
