      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is not a settled issue because \"root causes\" are incredibly complex and lack a single, easy-to-implement solution like a new law. While many studies point to the need for addressing systemic issues, the political will to enact large-scale social programs is often lacking. Therefore, the debate persists because different political factions prioritize different solutions—some focus on immediate punitive action, while others advocate for long-term social investment.",
